	<div id="comment_top_64659282" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a rel="nofollow" id="comment_link_64659282" name="comment_link_64659282" href="//tech.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23401972&amp;cid=64659282" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64659282)" >"Digital traps" otherwise known as</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64659282" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64659282); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>5</a>, Interesting)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Rosco+P.+Coltrane">Rosco P. Coltrane</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Rosco+P.+Coltrane">( 209368 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64659282">		
		on Saturday July 27, 2024 @02:09AM (<span class="ind"></span><a rel="nofollow" href="//tech.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23401972&amp;cid=64659282">#64659282</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64659282"><p>Watermarks.</p><p>And they're old as dirt. It's hardly a new idea.</p><p>I use them all the time to figure out who sells my data to whom. Whenever I sign up to something - willingly or not - I give my name with different middle initials, like John T. H. Doe, then the next submission, I put John T. I. Doe, then John T. K. Doe and I keep track of who I gave which name to.</p><p>When a name comes back on a piece of junk mail or spam email, I know who sold my information. If it's a company, I put them on my list of companies never to buy anything from again.</p><p>It works as long as whoever sold my information doesn't strip the fake middle initials, just like the "digital traps" will work if AI doesn't mangle the original works so much that the watermarks gets destroyed.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64659282">
<span class="ind"></span><a id="reply_link_64659282" class="btn link" href="//tech.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23401972&amp;op=Reply&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;pid=64659282" onclick="D2.replyTo(64659282); return false;">Reply to This</a> 	<a rel="nofollow" href="#" class="comment_share_toggle btn link">Share</a>
